Project Report : Salary vs Experience Correlation Analysis

1. Introduction
This project analyzes the relationship between years of experience and salary using correlation analysis. The goal is to understand how professional experience impacts salary growth and present insights through a Power BI dashboard.

2. Dataset Description
The dataset contains two variables: Years of Experience and Salary (INR per year). It consists of clean, structured data suitable for statistical analysis and dashboard visualization.

3. Tools & Technologies
•	Power BI Desktop for visualization
•	DAX for calculated measures
•	Excel/CSV as data source

4. Methodology
Correlation analysis was performed using Pearson’s correlation coefficient. Scatter plots and trend lines were used to visually analyze the relationship between salary and experience.

5. Dashboard Overview
The Power BI dashboard includes Slicers, salary and years experience along with a scatter plot and salary growth line chart.

6. Key Insights
•	There is a strong positive correlation between salary and years of experience.
•	Salary increases almost linearly as experience grows.
•	Experience is a significant factor influencing salary growth.

7. Conclusion
This analysis demonstrates that years of experience strongly influence salary levels. The Power BI dashboard effectively communicates these insights and can support HR and business decision-making.
